Each source directory can have one `#*.bst` file that marks it as a module.

### One root per folder

The filename after `#` does not matter. `#page.bst`, `#mod.bst` and `#api.bst` all mean the same thing. Two `#*.bst` files in one folder are rejected.

### Import the module, not the root file

You cannot import `#api.bst` directly. Import the module through its directory path to access its public surface.

### Two roles

When a module root is the active module being compiled, its top-level runtime code runs. When it is imported by another module, only its exported declarations are available. Its runtime code does not run.

### Remember

- One `#*.bst` file per directory.
- The `#` name is cosmetic.
- `config.bst` is not a module root.